208 #if defined(_WIN32) || (defined(__BYTE_ORDER__) && defined(__ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN__) && \
209  (__BYTE_ORDER__ == __ORDER_LITTLE_ENDIAN__))
210 # define UA_BINARY_OVERLAYABLE_INTEGER true
211 #elif defined(__ANDROID__) /* Andoid */
212 # include <endian.h>
213 # if __BYTE_ORDER == __LITTLE_ENDIAN
214 # define UA_BINARY_OVERLAYABLE_INTEGER true
215 # endif
216 #elif defined(__linux__) /* Linux */
217 # include <endian.h>
218 # if __BYTE_ORDER == __LITTLE_ENDIAN
219 # define UA_BINARY_OVERLAYABLE_INTEGER true
220 # endif
221 # if __FLOAT_BYTE_ORDER == __LITTLE_ENDIAN
222 # define UA_BINARY_OVERLAYABLE_FLOAT true
223 # endif
224 #elif defined(__OpenBSD__) /* OpenBSD */
225 # include <sys/endian.h>
226 # if BYTE_ORDER == LITTLE_ENDIAN
227 # define UA_BINARY_OVERLAYABLE_INTEGER true
228 # endif
229 #elif defined(__NetBSD__) || defined(__FreeBSD__) || defined(__DragonFly__) /* Other BSD */
230 # include <sys/endian.h>
231 # if _BYTE_ORDER == _LITTLE_ENDIAN
232 # define UA_BINARY_OVERLAYABLE_INTEGER true
233 # endif
234 #elif defined(__APPLE__) /* Apple (MacOS, iOS) */
235 # include <libkern/OSByteOrder.h>
236 # if defined(__LITTLE_ENDIAN__)
237 # define UA_BINARY_OVERLAYABLE_INTEGER true
238 # endif
239 #elif defined(__QNX__) || defined(__QNXNTO__) /* QNX */
240 # include <gulliver.h>
241 # if defined(__LITTLEENDIAN__)
242 # define UA_BINARY_OVERLAYABLE_INTEGER true
243 # endif
244 #endif

278 #if defined(__cplusplus) && __cplusplus >= 201103L /* C++11 or above */
279 # define UA_STATIC_ASSERT(cond,msg) static_assert(cond, #msg)
280 #elif defined(__STDC_VERSION__) && __STDC_VERSION__ >= 201112L /* C11 or above */
281 # define UA_STATIC_ASSERT(cond,msg) _Static_assert(cond, #msg)
282 #elif defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__) || defined(_MSC_VER) /* GCC, Clang, MSC */
283 # define UA_CTASTR2(pre,post) pre ## post
284 # define UA_CTASTR(pre,post) UA_CTASTR2(pre,post)
285 # define UA_STATIC_ASSERT(cond,msg) \
286  typedef struct { \
287  int UA_CTASTR(static_assertion_failed_,msg) : !!(cond); \
288  } UA_CTASTR(static_assertion_failed_,__COUNTER__)
289 #else /* Everybody else */
290 # define UA_STATIC_ASSERT(cond,msg) \
291  typedef char static_assertion_##msg[(cond)?1:-1]
292 #endif

344 // For Visual Studio 6 in C++ mode and for many Visual Studio versions when
345 // compiling for ARM we should wrap <wchar.h> include with 'extern "C++" {}'
346 // or compiler give many errors like this:
347 // error C2733: second C linkage of overloaded function 'wmemchr' not allowed

356 // Define _W64 macros to mark types changing their size, like intptr_t.
357 #ifndef _W64
358 # if !defined(__midl) && (defined(_X86_) || defined(_M_IX86)) && _MSC_VER >= 1300
359 # define _W64 __w64
360 # else
361 # define _W64

366 // 7.18.1 Integer types
367 
368 // 7.18.1.1 Exact-width integer types
369 
370 // Visual Studio 6 and Embedded Visual C++ 4 doesn't
371 // realize that, e.g. char has the same size as __int8
372 // so we give up on __intX for them.
373 #if (_MSC_VER < 1300)
374  typedef signed char int8_t;
375  typedef signed short int16_t;
376  typedef signed int int32_t;
377  typedef unsigned char uint8_t;
378  typedef unsigned short uint16_t;
379  typedef unsigned int uint32_t;
380 #else
381  typedef signed __int8 int8_t;
382  typedef signed __int16 int16_t;
383  typedef signed __int32 int32_t;
384  typedef unsigned __int8 uint8_t;
385  typedef unsigned __int16 uint16_t;
386  typedef unsigned __int32 uint32_t;
387 #endif
388 typedef signed __int64 int64_t;
389 typedef unsigned __int64 uint64_t;
390 
391 
392 // 7.18.1.2 Minimum-width integer types
393 typedef int8_t int_least8_t;
394 typedef int16_t int_least16_t;
395 typedef int32_t int_least32_t;
396 typedef int64_t int_least64_t;
397 typedef uint8_t uint_least8_t;
398 typedef uint16_t uint_least16_t;
399 typedef uint32_t uint_least32_t;
400 typedef uint64_t uint_least64_t;
401 
402 // 7.18.1.3 Fastest minimum-width integer types
403 typedef int8_t int_fast8_t;
404 typedef int16_t int_fast16_t;
405 typedef int32_t int_fast32_t;
406 typedef int64_t int_fast64_t;
407 typedef uint8_t uint_fast8_t;
408 typedef uint16_t uint_fast16_t;
409 typedef uint32_t uint_fast32_t;
410 typedef uint64_t uint_fast64_t;
411 
412 // 7.18.1.4 Integer types capable of holding object pointers
413 #ifdef _WIN64 // [
414  typedef signed __int64 intptr_t;
415  typedef unsigned __int64 uintptr_t;
416 #else // _WIN64 ][
417  typedef _W64 signed int intptr_t;
418  typedef _W64 unsigned int uintptr_t;
419 #endif // _WIN64 ]
420 
421 // 7.18.1.5 Greatest-width integer types
422 typedef int64_t intmax_t;
423 typedef uint64_t uintmax_t;

651 #define UA_STATUSCODE_GOOD 0x00
652 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADUNEXPECTEDERROR 0x80010000 // An unexpected error occurred.
653 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADINTERNALERROR 0x80020000 // An internal error occurred as a result of a programming or configuration error.
654 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADOUTOFMEMORY 0x80030000 // Not enough memory to complete the operation.
655 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADRESOURCEUNAVAILABLE 0x80040000 // An operating system resource is not available.
656 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADCOMMUNICATIONERROR 0x80050000 // A low level communication error occurred.
657 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADENCODINGERROR 0x80060000 // Encoding halted because of invalid data in the objects being serialized.
658 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADDECODINGERROR 0x80070000 // Decoding halted because of invalid data in the stream.
659 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADENCODINGLIMITSEXCEEDED 0x80080000 // The message encoding/decoding limits imposed by the stack have been exceeded.
660 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADREQUESTTOOLARGE 0x80b80000 // The request message size exceeds limits set by the server.
661 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADRESPONSETOOLARGE 0x80b90000 // The response message size exceeds limits set by the client.
662 #define UA_STATUSCODE_BADUNKNOWNRESPONSE 0x80090000 // An unrecognized response was received from the server.

1389 #define UA_EMPTY_ARRAY_SENTINEL ((void*)0x01)
1390 
1391 typedef enum {
1392  UA_VARIANT_DATA, /* The data has the same lifecycle as the
1393  variant */
1394  UA_VARIANT_DATA_NODELETE, /* The data is "borrowed" by the variant and
1395  shall not be deleted at the end of the
1396  variant's lifecycle. */
1397 } UA_VariantStorageType;
1398 
1399 typedef struct {
1400  const UA_DataType *type; /* The data type description */
1401  UA_VariantStorageType storageType;
1402  size_t arrayLength; /* The number of elements in the data array */
1403  void *data; /* Points to the scalar or array data */
1404  size_t arrayDimensionsSize; /* The number of dimensions */
1405  UA_UInt32 *arrayDimensions; /* The length of each dimension */
1406 } UA_Variant;
1407 
1408 /* Returns true if the variant has no value defined (contains neither an array
1409  * nor a scalar value).
1410  *
1411  * @param v The variant
1412  * @return Is the variant empty */
1413 static UA_INLINE UA_Boolean
1414 UA_Variant_isEmpty(const UA_Variant *v) {
1415  return v->type == NULL;
1416 }
1417 
1418 /* Returns true if the variant contains a scalar value. Note that empty variants
1419  * contain an array of length -1 (undefined).
1420  *
1421  * @param v The variant
1422  * @return Does the variant contain a scalar value */
1423 static UA_INLINE UA_Boolean
1424 UA_Variant_isScalar(const UA_Variant *v) {
1425  return (v->arrayLength == 0 && v->data > UA_EMPTY_ARRAY_SENTINEL);
1426 }
1427 
1428 /* Returns true if the variant contains a scalar value of the given type.
1429  *
1430  * @param v The variant
1431  * @param type The data type
1432  * @return Does the variant contain a scalar value of the given type */
1433 static UA_INLINE UA_Boolean
1434 UA_Variant_hasScalarType(const UA_Variant *v, const UA_DataType *type) {
1435  return UA_Variant_isScalar(v) && type == v->type;
1436 }
1437 
1438 /* Returns true if the variant contains an array of the given type.
1439  *
1440  * @param v The variant
1441  * @param type The data type
1442  * @return Does the variant contain an array of the given type */
1443 static UA_INLINE UA_Boolean
1444 UA_Variant_hasArrayType(const UA_Variant *v, const UA_DataType *type) {
1445  return (!UA_Variant_isScalar(v)) && type == v->type;
1446 }
1447 
1448 /* Set the variant to a scalar value that already resides in memory. The value
1449  * takes on the lifecycle of the variant and is deleted with it.
1450  *
1451  * @param v The variant
1452  * @param p A pointer to the value data
1453  * @param type The datatype of the value in question */
1454 void UA_EXPORT
1455 UA_Variant_setScalar(UA_Variant *v, void * UA_RESTRICT p,
1456  const UA_DataType *type);
1457 
1458 /* Set the variant to a scalar value that is copied from an existing variable.
1459  * @param v The variant
1460  * @param p A pointer to the value data
1461  * @param type The datatype of the value
1462  * @return Indicates whether the operation succeeded or returns an error code */
1463 UA_StatusCode UA_EXPORT
1464 UA_Variant_setScalarCopy(UA_Variant *v, const void *p,
1465  const UA_DataType *type);
1466 
1467 /* Set the variant to an array that already resides in memory. The array takes

1469  *
1470  * @param v The variant
1471  * @param array A pointer to the array data
1472  * @param arraySize The size of the array
1473  * @param type The datatype of the array */

9462 typedef enum {
9463  UA_CONNECTION_OPENING, /* The socket is open, but the HEL/ACK handshake
9464  is not done */
9465  UA_CONNECTION_ESTABLISHED, /* The socket is open and the connection
9466  configured */

9468  will be deleted */

9476 typedef struct UA_SecureChannel UA_SecureChannel;

9478 struct UA_Connection {
9479  UA_ConnectionState state;
9480  UA_ConnectionConfig localConf;
9481  UA_ConnectionConfig remoteConf;
9482  UA_SecureChannel *channel; /* The securechannel that is attached to
9483  this connection */
9484  UA_Int32 sockfd; /* Most connectivity solutions run on
9485  sockets. Having the socket id here
9486  simplifies the design. */
9487  void *handle; /* A pointer to internal data */
9488  UA_ByteString incompleteMessage; /* A half-received message (TCP is a
9489  streaming protocol) is stored here */
9490 
9491  /* Get a buffer for sending */
9492  UA_StatusCode (*getSendBuffer)(UA_Connection *connection, size_t length,
9493  UA_ByteString *buf);
9494 
9495  /* Release the send buffer manually */
9496  void (*releaseSendBuffer)(UA_Connection *connection, UA_ByteString *buf);
9497 
9498  /* Sends a message over the connection. The message buffer is always freed,
9499  * even if sending fails.
9500  *
9501  * @param connection The connection
9502  * @param buf The message buffer
9503  * @return Returns an error code or UA_STATUSCODE_GOOD. */
9504  UA_StatusCode (*send)(UA_Connection *connection, UA_ByteString *buf);
9505 
9506  /* Receive a message from the remote connection
9507  *
9508  * @param connection The connection
9509  * @param response The response string. It is allocated by the connection
9510  * and needs to be freed with connection->releaseBuffer
9511  * @param timeout Timeout of the recv operation in milliseconds
9512  * @return Returns UA_STATUSCODE_BADCOMMUNICATIONERROR if the recv operation
9513  * can be repeated, UA_STATUSCODE_GOOD if it succeeded and
9514  * UA_STATUSCODE_BADCONNECTIONCLOSED if the connection was
9515  * closed. */
9516  UA_StatusCode (*recv)(UA_Connection *connection, UA_ByteString *response,
9517  UA_UInt32 timeout);
9518 
9519  /* Release the buffer of a received message */
9520  void (*releaseRecvBuffer)(UA_Connection *connection, UA_ByteString *buf);
9521 
9522  /* Close the connection */
9523  void (*close)(UA_Connection *connection);
9524 };

9571 struct UA_Server;
9572 typedef struct UA_Server UA_Server;
9573 
9574 typedef void (*UA_ServerCallback)(UA_Server *server, void *data);
9575 
9576 /* Jobs describe work that is executed once or repeatedly in the server */
9577 typedef struct {
9578  enum {
9579  UA_JOBTYPE_NOTHING,
9580  UA_JOBTYPE_DETACHCONNECTION, /* Detach the connection from the secure channel (but don't delete it) */
9581  UA_JOBTYPE_BINARYMESSAGE_NETWORKLAYER, /* The binary message is memory managed by the networklayer */
9582  UA_JOBTYPE_BINARYMESSAGE_ALLOCATED, /* The binary message was relocated away from the networklayer */
9583  UA_JOBTYPE_METHODCALL, /* Call the method as soon as possible */
9584  UA_JOBTYPE_METHODCALL_DELAYED, /* Call the method as soon as all previous jobs have finished */
9585  } type;
9586  union {
9587  UA_Connection *closeConnection;
9588  struct {
9589  UA_Connection *connection;
9590  UA_ByteString message;
9591  } binaryMessage;
9592  struct {
9593  void *data;
9594  UA_ServerCallback method;
9595  } methodCall;
9596  } job;
9597 } UA_Job;

9600 } // extern "C"

9762 struct UA_ServerNetworkLayer;
9763 typedef struct UA_ServerNetworkLayer UA_ServerNetworkLayer;
9764 
9765 struct UA_ServerNetworkLayer {
9766  void *handle; // pointer to internal data
9767  UA_String discoveryUrl;
9768 
9769  /* Starts listening on the the networklayer.
9770  *
9771  * @param nl The network layer
9772  * @param logger The logger
9773  * @return Returns UA_STATUSCODE_GOOD or an error code. */
9774  UA_StatusCode (*start)(UA_ServerNetworkLayer *nl, UA_Logger logger);
9775 
9776  /* Gets called from the main server loop and returns the jobs (accumulated
9777  * messages and close events) for dispatch.
9778  *
9779  * @param nl The network layer
9780  * @param jobs When the returned integer is >0, *jobs points to an array of
9781  * UA_Job of the returned size.
9782  * @param timeout The timeout during which an event must arrive in
9783  * microseconds
9784  * @return The size of the jobs array. If the result is negative,
9785  * an error has occurred. */
9786  size_t (*getJobs)(UA_ServerNetworkLayer *nl, UA_Job **jobs, UA_UInt16 timeout);
9787 
9788  /* Closes the network connection and returns all the jobs that need to be
9789  * finished before the network layer can be safely deleted.
9790  *
9791  * @param nl The network layer
9792  * @param jobs When the returned integer is >0, jobs points to an array of
9793  * UA_Job of the returned size.
9794  * @return The size of the jobs array. If the result is negative,
9795  * an error has occurred. */
9796  size_t (*stop)(UA_ServerNetworkLayer *nl, UA_Job **jobs);
9797 
9799  void (*deleteMembers)(UA_ServerNetworkLayer *nl);
9800 };

9871 /* Runs the main loop of the server. In each iteration, this calls into the
9872  * networklayers to see if jobs have arrived and checks if repeated jobs need to
9873  * be triggered.
9874  *
9875  * @param server The server object.
9876  * @param running The loop is run as long as *running is true.
9877  * Otherwise, the server shuts down.
9878  * @return Returns the statuscode of the UA_Server_run_shutdown method */

9880 UA_Server_run(UA_Server *server, volatile UA_Boolean *running);

9885 
9886 /* Executes a single iteration of the server's main loop.
9887  *
9888  * @param server The server object.
9889  * @param waitInternal Should we wait for messages in the networklayer?
9890  * Otherwise, the timouts for the networklayers are set to zero.

9892  * @return Returns how long we can wait until the next scheduled
9893  * job (in millisec) */
9894 UA_UInt16 UA_EXPORT

10297 typedef struct {
10298  void *handle; /* A custom pointer to reuse the same datasource functions for
10299  multiple sources */
10300  /* Copies the data from the source into the provided value.
10301  *
10302  * @param handle An optional pointer to user-defined data for the
10303  * specific data source
10304  * @param nodeid Id of the read node
10305  * @param includeSourceTimeStamp If true, then the datasource is expected to
10306  * set the source timestamp in the returned value
10307  * @param range If not null, then the datasource shall return only a
10308  * selection of the (nonscalar) data. Set
10309  * UA_STATUSCODE_BADINDEXRANGEINVALID in the value if this does not
10310  * apply.
10311  * @param value The (non-null) DataValue that is returned to the client. The
10312  * data source sets the read data, the result status and optionally a
10313  * sourcetimestamp.
10314  * @return Returns a status code for logging. Error codes intended for the
10315  * original caller are set in the value. If an error is returned,
10316  * then no releasing of the value is done. */
10317  UA_StatusCode (*read)(void *handle, const UA_NodeId nodeid,
10318  UA_Boolean includeSourceTimeStamp,
10319  const UA_NumericRange *range, UA_DataValue *value);
10320 
10321  /* Write into a data source. The write member of UA_DataSource can be empty
10322  * if the operation is unsupported.
10323  *
10324  * @param handle An optional pointer to user-defined data for the
10325  * specific data source
10326  * @param nodeid Id of the node being written to
10327  * @param data The data to be written into the data source
10328  * @param range An optional data range. If the data source is scalar or does
10329  * not support writing of ranges, then an error code is returned.
10330  * @return Returns a status code that is returned to the user
10331  */
10332  UA_StatusCode (*write)(void *handle, const UA_NodeId nodeid,
10333  const UA_Variant *data, const UA_NumericRange *range);
10334 } UA_DataSource;

10347 typedef struct {
10348  /* Pointer to user-provided data for the callback */
10349  void *handle;
10350 
10351  /* Called before the value attribute is read. It is possible to write into the
10352  * value attribute during onRead (using the write service). The node is
10353  * re-opened afterwards so that changes are considered in the following read
10354  * operation.
10355  *
10356  * @param handle Points to user-provided data for the callback.
10357  * @param nodeid The identifier of the node.
10358  * @param data Points to the current node value.
10359  * @param range Points to the numeric range the client wants to read from
10360  * (or NULL). */
10361  void (*onRead)(void *handle, const UA_NodeId nodeid,
10362  const UA_Variant *data, const UA_NumericRange *range);
10363 
10364  /* Called after writing the value attribute. The node is re-opened after
10365  * writing so that the new value is visible in the callback.
10366  *
10367  * @param handle Points to user-provided data for the callback.
10368  * @param nodeid The identifier of the node.
10369  * @param data Points to the current node value (after writing).
10370  * @param range Points to the numeric range the client wants to write to (or
10371  * NULL). */
10372  void (*onWrite)(void *handle, const UA_NodeId nodeid,
10373  const UA_Variant *data, const UA_NumericRange *range);
10374 } UA_ValueCallback;

10667 typedef enum {
10668  UA_CLIENTSTATE_READY, /* The client is not connected but initialized
10669  and ready to use. */
10670  UA_CLIENTSTATE_CONNECTED, /* The client is connected to a server. */
10671  UA_CLIENTSTATE_FAULTED, /* An error has occured that might have
10672  influenced the connection state. A successfull
10673  service call or renewal of the secure channel
10674  will reset the state to CONNECTED. */
10675  UA_CLIENTSTATE_ERRORED /* A non-recoverable error has occured and the
10676  connection is no longer reliable. The client
10677  needs to be disconnected and reinitialized to
10678  recover into a CONNECTED state. */
10679 } UA_ClientState;

10779 #ifdef UA_ENABLE_METHODCALLS
